# Error Handling

**📚 Complete Guide**: `ai-rules/conventions/error-handling.md`

## Critical Rules
- **Always use domain errors** from `@dfs/common/domain`, never `new Error()`
- **TRPC integration**: Domain errors are automatically mapped to TRPC errors via middleware
- **Extend base errors**: Bounded contexts create their own errors by extending base domain errors

## Error Types

| Error | Status | When to Use |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| `ValidationError` | 400 | Invalid input, format errors |
| `UnauthorizedError` | 401 | Missing/invalid auth |
| `ForbiddenError` | 403 | Insufficient permissions |
| `NotFoundError` | 404 | Resource not found |
| `ConflictError` | 409 | Duplicate resource |
| `BusinessRuleError` | 422 | Business logic violations |

## Quick Examples

```typescript
import { NotFoundError, ValidationError, ConflictError } from '@dfs/common/domain'

// Validation
throw new ValidationError('Email is required', 'email')
throw ValidationError.invalidFormat('email', value)

// Not found
throw NotFoundError.withId('User', id)

// Conflict
throw ConflictError.alreadyExists('User', email)
```

